>> What are two shortcomings of RNNs compared to transformers?<<

[x] A. Not easy to parallelize  {{ selected: A. Correct. Since each timestep takes the previous timestep's information as input, each hidden state must be computed sequentially. }}
[ ] B. Fixed hidden state bottleneck  {{ selected: B. Incorrect, this is a problem with vanilla seq2seq models }}
[x] C. Struggle to capture very long term dependencies {{ selected: C. Correct. The hidden state (which is a matrix of fixed size) can only hold so much information.}}
[ ] D. Vanishing gradients {{ selected: D. Incorrect, this is not one of the shortcomings compared to transformers; however, this could be a problem with vanilla RNNs with long sequences }}

